============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is the Renaissance?
A1: The Renaissance (14th-17th century) was a cultural
     rebirth in Europe featuring renewed interest in Greco-
     Roman art, humanism, and early science. Began in Italy;
     spread across Europe.

Q2: What is natural selection?
A2: Natural selection: individuals with traits better
     suited to their environment survive and reproduce more.
     Over many generations, these traits become more common
     in the population.

Q3: What is metabolism?
A3: Metabolism is all chemical reactions in an organism
     that maintain life: catabolism (breaking molecules for
     energy) and anabolism (building complex molecules from
     simple ones).

Q4: What is capitalism?
A4: Capitalism is an economic system where private
     individuals own the means of production and markets
     determine prices and production through supply and
     demand.

Q5: What is DNA?
A5: DNA (deoxyribonucleic acid) is a double helix molecule
     that carries genetic information. It consists of base
     pairs: adenine-thymine and guanine-cytosine.

